    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 2002 BMW M3 is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54 inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and a 8,000 RPM redline. The powertrain is mated to a Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission, delivering drive to the rear wheels via a variable M-differential lock. The chassis remains composed with a recently inspected rear subframe and refreshed bushings, ensuring the integrity of the multi-link rear suspension. The dual-VANOS variable valve timing system has been meticulously maintained to preserve the engine's broad torque curve. While the exterior shows honest signs of road use, the mechanical vitals are robust, making this an ideal candidate for an enthusiast seeking peak E46 performance without the premium of a garage queen.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
